data.enText: if sb/sth has a particular tendency , they are likely to behave or act in a particular way

data.chText: 显示出对艺术等的偏好

data.enText: I have a tendency to talk too much when I'm nervous.

data.chText: 这种疾病易在家族里遗传。
data.enText: There is a tendency for this disease to run in families.
She has a strong natural tendency towards caution.
a new custom that is starting to develop

data.chText: 雇主雇用临时职员有增加的趋势。
data.enText: There is a growing tendency among employers to hire casual staff.

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a group within a larger political group, whose views are more extreme than those of the rest of the group

simple_means.memory_skill: tend 趋向 + ency 状态，行为 → 趋向

tr: a characteristic likelihood of or natural disposition toward a certain condition or character or effect
example: the alkaline inclination of the local waters
fabric with a tendency to shrink

tr: an attitude of mind especially one that favors one alternative over others
example: he had an inclination to give up too easily
a tendency to be too strict

tr: a general direction in which something tends to move
example: the shoreward tendency of the current
the trend of the stock market

value.def: A tendency is a worrying or unpleasant habit or action that keeps occurring.

example.ex: The army has become increasingly restless over the mounting separatist tendencies of the northern republics.
example.tran: 军方对于北方几个共和国不断加剧的分裂倾向感到越来越不安。

example.ex: ...the government's tendency towards secrecy in recent years.
example.tran: 近年来政府的保密倾向

value.tran: (令人焦虑或不快的)习惯，经常性行为，倾向

value.def: A tendency is a part of your character that makes you behave in an unpleasant or worrying way.

example.ex: He is spoiled, arrogant and has a tendency towards snobbery...
example.tran: 他被宠坏了，傲慢无礼，而且经常自命不凡。

example.ex: Helen had been struggling against suicidal tendencies.
example.tran: 海伦一直在压制心里的自杀念头。

trans: 集中趋势(变量的值接近其平均值的趋势)
